we are passing list of product.

12
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,870
On top of that, we need to pass list of all the categories

13
00:00:39,870 --> 00:00:42,930
or we can pass a select list that we can use

14
00:00:42,930 --> 00:00:44,703
to populate a dropdown.

15
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:48,690
Now, there are multiple ways to pass that thing.

16
00:00:48,690 --> 00:00:51,990
But if we want to pass that along with this object,

17
00:00:51,990 --> 00:00:54,930
that is not possible because when we return back,

18
00:00:54,930 --> 00:00:57,900
we can only pass one object.

19
00:00:57,900 --> 00:01:01,380
We will see how to overcome that in the upcoming videos.

20
00:01:01,380 --> 00:01:04,560
But let's say you only want to return a list of product

21
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:06,780
and not any other model.

22
00:01:06,780 --> 00:01:07,613
In that case,

23
00:01:07,613 --> 00:01:10,470
if we have to pass some additional functionalities,

24
00:01:10,470 --> 00:01:12,360
there are many other ways,

25
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:14,880
but before we see how to pass that,

26
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:17,013
we actually have to retrieve that.

27
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:21,900
So, to retrieve that, I will store that in an IEnumerable

28
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:24,183
of select list item.

29
00:01:25,072 --> 00:01:26,649
If I press control dot here,

30
00:01:26,649 --> 00:01:30,870
it is inside system.collections.generic,

31
00:01:30,870 --> 00:01:34,650
that is the IEnumerable that select list item

32
00:01:34,650 --> 00:01:39,650
is inside Microsoft.aspnetcore.mbc.rendering.

33
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:44,550
Now if I press F12 on the select list item,

34
00:01:44,550 --> 00:01:47,070
it'll navigate me to the class here

35
00:01:47,070 --> 00:01:49,830
and you can see with the select list item,

36
00:01:49,830 --> 00:01:52,020
we have text and value

37
00:01:52,020 --> 00:01:54,780
and that is what we will be populating

38
00:01:54,780 --> 00:01:56,763
and using in our dropdown.

39
00:01:58,380 --> 00:02:02,220
So, let me call this category list is equal to.

40
00:02:02,220 --> 00:02:04,350
We need to retrieve all the categories,

41
00:02:04,350 --> 00:02:06,993
so unit of work.category.getall.

42
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:11,820
And then if we just do that, it will not work

43
00:02:11,820 --> 00:02:16,290
because here, it is retrieving an IEnumerable of category

44
00:02:16,290 --> 00:02:19,500
and we have to convert that to an IEnumerable

45
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,783
of select list item.

46
00:02:22,980 --> 00:02:25,530
How can we do that dynamic conversion,

47
00:02:25,530 --> 00:02:29,520
while we are recreating some things from the database?

48
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:32,820
In order to do that, we have something powerful,

49
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:35,943
known as projections in EF Core.

50
00:02:37,170 --> 00:02:41,040
In order to use projections, we will say .select

51
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:43,650
and there, we will give it a random object.

52
00:02:43,650 --> 00:02:45,390
Let me call that U.

53
00:02:45,390 --> 00:02:48,990
And what object do we want to return from here?

54
00:02:48,990 --> 00:02:53,010
We want to return a new select list item.

55
00:02:53,010 --> 00:02:55,830
So, we will write that and inside there,

56
00:02:55,830 --> 00:02:59,340
what properties should be populated?

57
00:02:59,340 --> 00:03:02,070
Let me break it out in different line here.

58
00:03:02,070 --> 00:03:04,350
We want to populate the text,

59
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:07,590
which is inside u.Name and value,

60
00:03:07,590 --> 00:03:12,210
we want ID of the category, so U.Id,

61
00:03:12,210 --> 00:03:14,163
convert that to a string.

62
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:18,990
That way what will happen is each category object here

63
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:22,350
will be converted into a select list item

64
00:03:22,350 --> 00:03:25,350
and it will have a text and a value.

65
00:03:25,350 --> 00:03:28,410
And that is how we can convert a category

66
00:03:28,410 --> 00:03:33,410
to an IEnumerable of select list item using projection.

67
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:36,900
Again, this is very powerful feature

68
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:39,330
because you can see how in a single line

69
00:03:39,330 --> 00:03:41,250
when you are retrieving something,

70
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:44,100
you can easily pick only some columns

71
00:03:44,100 --> 00:03:46,230
and not all the columns.

72
00:03:46,230 --> 00:03:48,720
You can convert that to a new object

73
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:50,673
and directly assign that.

74
00:03:51,510 --> 00:03:55,080
With that, we have the category list right here.

75
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:56,490
But now the question is,

76
00:03:56,490 --> 00:04:00,000
